{"title":"Women’s Cycling Weekly: Issue 24","link":"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/05/womens-cycling-weekly-issue-24/","date":1620407382000,"content":"<p>Hello! Welcome to Women’s Cycling Weekly issue 24 🚴‍♀️</p>\n\n\n\n<p>No broken down cars this time but instead it’s been one of those weeks where my brain feels like it’s juddering to a halt at about 3pm every day — can I call a tow truck for that and do you reckon my insurance will cover it? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Although there’s lots of racing happening with Elsy Jacobs last week and Setmana Ciclista Valenciana this week it still feels like we’re in some kind of liminal space as we wait for the next round of the WWT. Maybe that’s exacerbated by the deafening fanfare of the Giro d’Italia that’s drowning out almost everything else in the cycling world this week (a good time to remind ourselves about <a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVkU2OwyAMhU9Tdo34CYQsWMxmrhEReG1RCYmATJXbD5nOppJtWXq2nvXZ2Yr7mg-zraWSs0z12GASXiWiVmSyF-QpeMMVH2nPR-JN75mWmoQy3TKw2BBNzTvIts8xOFvDms4NIbnm5GFGbnutqIQUHo55LZ0YJaxTjELp8e1rdx-QHAx-kI81gUTzqHUrF_F14d8tFruEmLEhRuSu7HOp1j07ty5N3Fq-1gWpXN3hYkj36wt4xuMaStlxZZIEwylnVNKBKaZ63bHuRjELDjr0DgO3glPIgXGhlRhudpaXni53_uFFsrHzfHRLcE8cbeDfroatnHpn9xPE1NplT6EeE5KdI_ybUX2j_qM23ZGQ2wv8ZKthitO-EWajlPTN5ISoWC8GLUm7wa9tK5kPDr8b3pgC\">Alfonsina Strada</a>). But fear not WCW reader, this is a Giro-free corner of cycling content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You know the drill by now, thanks to CyclingTips for supporting WCW and women’s cycling! If you’re reading on CT and you like emails (nice ones only!) then you can <a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVUdtqxSAQ_Jr41uAlmuTBh0LpbwQvm1QaTdC1JX9f09MWCrKgM4OzM84gbEe-9HkUJPdY8DpBJ_gsOyBCJrVAXoLXXPGZDnwmXg-eTXIioSxrBogm7BpzBXJWuwdnMBzpVgjJJ07etJGrUYry0fvZSfCzn9gETonVwczt_PjXVB8gOdDwAfk6EpBdvyGepRPPHX9tJ5oY9gwn7DvkvlRb0Lj33h2xgffV5WChE42rKsYlgg81duLl2-LPYzlqdo308id4-gx-A_zB3ZEQEjaCUGwQ4yRJ0JxyRiUdmWJqmHrWrxSs4EDHwcHIjeAU5Mi4mJQYV2NlN9C48X8eSdbG2quPwb3D1QjucntIG4az3Hhv6h1gMxBjTQGvBZKxO_hHtvio6HuVZYMEuVXnF4OaKU6H1gybpaSPLO_wf903D_5oqqT_5fcFC4yrjw\" target=\"_blank\">subscribe</a> to WCW and get the whole thing in your inbox as well.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>News 📰</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Some <a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJwtkMtuxCAMRb9mWEa8IQsW3fQ3IgLODBpCIh4d5e8LTSXLsmX7-uo4W-F55MucR6lopKVeJ5gEnxKhVsioFchL8IZKOmNOZ-QN90QLjUJZtgyw2xBNzQ3Q2dYYnK3hSOOCCaopehnLJQcPetu81AxbScS2SSGFZ0pqTe6_tvkAyYGBH8jXkQBF86r1LA_29aDfPeonDEeTO_beucvFkJ6bTaV3pdraRkGYnue5q5PuVijMFEHBUEwJFlgRSSTXE5k2DCujgBV3oKhlFINQhDItmdrsKh4c7086lbZ2ZfceP1E2dl2vaQ_uDVdf-HdQw1nGfLJtEFh6ubcU6rVAsmsEf8OpN-M_XMsTEuTO3i-2GiIp5h0tmYXAN4xBTxLOlBaoe_BHv0pmt3uIGU6IEfIv3BaSIQ\">news of unconfirmed </a>validity regarding the <strong>women’s Tour de France</strong> — a crumb, if you will, from our overlords at ASO. </li><li>In other crumb-shaped news, a <a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJwtkMtuhDAMRb9mskR5Elhk0U1_A5nEMFHzQEnoiL9vmKlk2ZbsK_seCw33XC5z5NrInZZ2HWgSvmrA1rCQs2JZvDN85DOVfCbOSMcmNRFfl60gRvDBtHIiOc41eAvN53QrhOITJ0-zgqITl8DGbVOCznScNXCNarNaW0k_d-F0HpNFg79YrpyQBPNs7agP8fXg3z1er9ew-5KdbxA8uJwSDr71yTs9c8ReiDecckYV1Wxko5wGNmwUV8GRamlRcxCcotKMi2kUeoNVPSSNOx_qudYG9mewOZJiYF2vIXr7g1dfsJcNPu3NH_WeD3DefpfexjP5di2YYA3oPijah-gbzrJjwtJJuwWaYSOnsoNks1L_1m9WI5NCT4r0H1zuqmQiRB8KHhgClj8MMY35\">website</a> has popped up containing apparent details of the 2021 <strong>Giro Rosa</strong>, including a promise of 30 minutes of daily live coverage. There has been no confirmation as to whether it’s official. But I’m reporting it anyway, ok? </li><li><strong>Ayesha McGowan</strong> has announced the recipients of her <strong>Thee Abundance Mini-Grant</strong>. The nine chosen riders will receive support while racing the Tour of America’s Dairyland in June. The grant recipients are, Gabriella Allong, Rachel Parker, Guarina Lopez, Bijou Vaultz, Carissa Yao, Valeria Diaz, Ajoa Abrokwa, Nicole Young, and Uhllana Woods. Find out more via McGowan’s website, <a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJwlkNFuhSAMhp_mcGmggOAFF7vZaxiE6iFDdIBzvv1wJk3TpP37t5-zFZctX2bfSiV3Guu1o0l4loi1YiZHwTwGb6CHgQoYiDfCMy01CWWcM-JqQzQ1H0j2Y4rB2Rq2dCu4BA3kbcQwcNZzZr1ymgGljHLJNSoU0oKCx9cePmByaPAH87UlJNG8a93Li3-84LPFeZ6d_T6C-5rydqZ5--3ctrZGtetCggEKjEqqWM96oTvWzRQnDkiVcKjAcqAoFQOue65mO8mXoOsCXTmmUq37ureRbOw0Xd3aXPBqA-5yMaSlhr3c_c4e95tjK9cjhXqNmOwU0T8E6gPyn8m4YMLcAPvRVsN6oKLxY4OU9Pn4RtQzwZWWpN3gt6ZKZrVriBl3jBHzH6czis8\">here</a>. </li><li><strong>The Cyclists’ Alliance</strong> have <a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJwlkElqxDAQRU_TWhrNshZahECuYTSUOyKybKRyGt8-chqKoj41fV70CM-9Xe7YO5I7LXgd4Cq8egFEaOTs0JacHNfcUsktSU4mNquZ5L6sDWDzuThsJ5DjDCVHj3mv94ZQfObk2xmahLJBg5FyjVbYVSYNniYT9TpDeP_1Z8pQIzj4hXbtFUhx34hHf4iPB_8aga98O5rivg31ecWSO_blo5QhO3o8-yiYsFRpa40SSmqr9MxIdpxyRhU1TDMt54lNK4UgOFAjIxjuBaegDONi1sKsPqiHpNuTT_0M43L8uZ-S5nwI17Tl-APXGIi3hfrEfPS7P_nzRrCMcjtrxmuB6kOB9KaDb8j_vJYnVGgDflo8OqY5lYMts0rRN40bn2ZSmFmR4SHtY6u6zW-5NDigFGh__peS7Q\">officially launched their mentorship programme</a>.</li><li>If you like virtual riding then you might be interested in the <a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJwlkEluxCAQAF8z3GKxGx845JJvWBjaHhQMFstMnNcHx1Kr1ftS1lTYUj71kUpFl5rreYCO8C4BaoWMWoE8e6eppBPmdEJOc0eUUMiXec0Au_FB19wAHW0J3prqU7w6mKCKoqcmQKSRkyQrU2wauVoVSDERhykobJZ7r2nOQ7Sg4QX5TBFQ0M9aj_Jgnw_61eX37dfqY_EO8mDT3kOv9FNTyx8UU9Jd5PVlYYFHIonkaiDDimFhFPDILYzUMIpBjIQyJdm4mkU8ON43OpS2lGrs9zUYZW2W5Rx2b7_h7AX2tMHHrfqjXPnBtOvXuZt7i76eM0SzBHA3hnrT_AczbxAhd8puNlUTSTHvEMkkBL7fvjhJwtmoBOo3uNS7ot7N7kOGA0KA_AdUDIwi\">VoxTour </a>organised by Voxwomen which began this week and runs until the 16th May. </li><li>If you’re UK-based then maybe you fancy helping more women get on bikes? <strong>British Cycling’s Breeze</strong> are looking for<a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJwlkEmO7CAMhk9TLCMgTFmw6E1fI2JwqlABiRhelNs_0pEsy_L4-3OmwXsvlz722tDt1nYdoDOcNUJrUFCvUNbgNRV0wYwuyGvmieIKhbpuBSCZEHUrHdDRbQzOtLDne2LmVFH00UpgzoA78AyU5YsCIf3G5UYWRvHin7um-wDZgYZ_UK49A4r609pRX_PPi_4OO89zGqJqCR4mt0_9O5IWjPuYdIybKGiKKcEcSyKIYGoi04bBzhSwZA4kNTPFwCWhsxKz3IzlL4bTm06129qM-461CRVtrL2mFNwXrtHgLhdDfrdw1Ls-mX5_uo4w9RzatUI2NoJ_ILSH5R-W9Q0ZymDsV9M0ERSzgZAsnOPn6ZuSIGyWiqOhwe9jKutkUogFDogRyn9w5IzA\"> ride leaders.</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Results 🏆</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Emma Norsgaard</strong> took her first win for <strong>Movistar</strong> at <strong>Festival Elsy Jacobs 1.Pro</strong> last weekend in emphatic style. The 21-year-old Danish rider won both road stages — and subsequently the GC — after fellow sprinter <strong>Lorena Wiebes </strong>(<strong>DSM</strong>) crashed out of the first stage after winning the prologue. Wiebes’s teammate <strong>Leah Kirchmann</strong> took second and <strong>Maria Giulia Confalonieri</strong> of <strong>Ceratizit-WNT</strong> third. If you fancy watching a recap then you can find all of the stages on YouTube: <a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJwlkMlqxDAMhp8mPgavWQ4-FMrQW889BdtRMqaOk3qZ4D59nQaEJCT9SPqMSrDuochjjwldbkrlAOnhjA5SgoByhDDZWdKOjpjTEc2Sz2QQA7JxWgLApqyTKWRAR9bOGpXs7i8FE3Sg6CmXcSSMjKYGA4QawIKzfhwx48Rg0d17VZ4teAMSXhDK7gE5-UzpiA17a-ij2nmebdlzyhpas29XRSXzbNjj1bD3_PM7M_P5OD6-kJUUU4IF7klHOj60pF0waEYB99xATxWjGERPKBs61i9Ki4bjbaVtzDomZb6vBShIpXVpN2u-odQBU4yzfk32iFe_Vfl6earplr1NZQKvtIP5ppFuqP98phU8hAp7nlSSpKOYV5ZkFALf31-4OlKxDALVG-a9qrzc1GZdgAOcg_AH7ZiOSQ\">Stage 1 video</a>. <a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJwlkMtuhDAMRb-GLFEe5MEii1aj-YVK3aDEeGbSCQGFpIi_LxTJsizbV9c-4Ao-57zbZV4LOdNQ9gVtwm2NWApmUlfMQxgtV7ynHe_JaLuRGWlIWIdHRpxciLbkimSpPgZwJczpVAjJDScv64wAkIIBA63VoaRAXa96yrXqoOeXr6tjwARo8RfzPick0b5KWdZGfDT8fsS2be0-11I9tjBPZ8cVeDXi_tuI2_apzBZvX98_QILllDMqqWaKqc60rH1Q9IIj1R2g5k5wilIzLowS-uG8bDo6PXm7Vr8WB-_TgGTrvN_bKcAb92MBdoghPUtY1nPeunq-PBzlVFMo-4DJ-YjjRaNcUP_5DE9MmA_Y4-CKZYrT7mDJeinp9f2JS7FOaCPJccM4H6pkJzeFmHHBGDH_AffgjkM\">Stage 2 video</a>. <a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJwlkM2OhSAMhZ9GlgYKiC5YTDJzH-FuDUJVMogG4RrffnRMmqbpT07PZ03GaU2n3tY9kzv1-dxQRzz2gDljImXH1HunoYGOCuiI08KxVrbE7_2YEBfjg86pINnKELw12a_xvuASWiCzBtUgZeA