g the race solo with a gap — which stretched to over two minutes at one point — but the American was eventually brought back and the stage culminated in a sprint finish won by <strong>Sandra Alonso</strong> of <strong>Bizkaia Durango</strong> with <strong>Sheyla Gutierrez </strong>of <strong>Movistar</strong> in second and <strong>Arianna Fidanza </strong>of <strong>Team BikeExchange</strong> in third.<br /><br /><strong>Omer Shapira</strong> of <strong>Canyon//SRAM</strong> leads both the QOM and sprint classifications. <br /></li><li>The first <strong>MTB XC World Cup</strong> of the season kicked off today in <strong>Albstadt, Germany </strong>World Champion <strong>Pauline Ferrand Prevot</strong> won the short track race this afternoon with <strong>Linda Indergand</strong> second and <strong>Annie Last</strong> in third.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Upcoming Races <strong>📅</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Setmana Ciclista Valenciana 2.1</strong> continues this weekend with the final two stages. Tomorrow’s stage is from Sagunt – València (108km) starting at 13:00 CET and the final stage on Sunday traverses Finestrat – Alacant (114km) starting at 12:00 CET. Race preview <a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJwtkUGOhCAQRU_T7NpACYgLFrOZaxjA0iaNaADbePvBdhIClZ9fVT8PZwrOazr1tuZCrmso54Y64pEDloKJ7BnT4EcNEnrKoSej5iNTQhGfhykhLsYHXdKOZNtt8M4Uv8aroxWggLz01HPKlBJgnXRUdZJZDkwKRSeHgP291-yjx-hQ4wfTuUYkQb9K2fKj_XnAbz3HcTTudMHH-crXuHWpajIOc30zlsVE83S-OnIxz48JdZ6_NKDAqmVL-PF41Ip4fWlU0I5JJrlqWDNRtC0g7bjDDkwLFEXHoFWy7SZjxYPTZYYm77ZOd-9rPUnaWHs2i3dvPKvhP17x2zdeY_YLylDLZY--nANGYwOON69yY_8SHGaMmOp3jIMpmkmgvNJmvRD05nMBlYy3nRKkZhjX2hX1YhYfEm4YAqY_Of-a9A\">here</a>. Live coverage via À Punt Media <a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJwlkUuOwyAMhk9TdkU8AkkWLGYz14gccFo0hETgtMrth7SSZVl-_dZnD4SPrZxu3yqxy0107ugyvmtCIizsqFimGJyyahSdGllwXZCDGVis01IQV4jJUTmQ7cecogeKW74mtFGDYk8nALQEGcwyyzB32lpl9TD2o7JeS2-_unCEiNmjwxeWc8vIknsS7fWmf27qt9n7_eawH5lWDBE41pYLsaAnbNFrSwR3v61HjgR0f0Fq6yJkuC-4xox1